            "latex": "",
            "html": "<html>\nThe image you provided does not contain a table but rather a flowchart comparing the architectures of VGG-19, a 34-layer plain network, and a 34-layer residual network. However, I can describe the structure of each network based on the flowchart.\n\nHere's a textual description of the architecture for each network:\n\n### VGG-19\n1. **Input Image**: Size: 224x224\n2. **Convolutional Layers**:\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Pooling layer (max pooling) with stride 2\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Pooling layer (max pooling) with stride 2\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n3. **Fully Connected Layers**:\n   - Fully connected layer with 4096 units\n   - Fully connected layer with 1000 units\n\n### 34-Layer Plain Network\n1. **Input Image**: Size: 224x224\n2. **Convolutional Layers**:\n   - Convolution with kernel size 7x7, filters 64\n   - Pooling layer (max pooling) with stride 2\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n3. **Fully Connected Layers**:\n   - Average pooling layer\n   - Fully connected layer with 1000 units\n\n### 34-Layer Residual Network\n1. **Input Image**: Size: 224x224\n2. **Convolutional Layers**:\n   - Convolution with kernel size 7x7, filters 64\n   - Pooling layer (max pooling) with stride 2\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 64\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 128\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 256\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n   - Convolution with kernel size 3x3, filters 512\n3. **Residual Connections**:\n   - Residual connections are shown as dotted lines connecting the input to the output of certain convolutional layers.\n4. **Fully Connected Layers**:\n   - Average pooling layer\n   - Fully connected layer with 1000 units\n\nIf you need the table in HTML format, please let me know how you would like it structured.\n</html>",
